Another Father’s Day in the books. 
Today was a good Father’s Day. 
To be honest, on most holidays such as this, I get a bit of anxiety because I love my children so much and I know it’s areas I can improve in to better their lives... 
Today I shook that off and enjoyed myself and took in how blessed I am to be the father of my awesome children!!
Happy Father’s Day Jonathan!! We are truly grateful for all that you do for this family! We hope you felt the love and appreciation today but most importantly all throughout the year. 🥰😘😘

I created a lifestyle based around the things that I love. 
I’ve had a very unique set of life experiences that have trained me to expect the worst of situations as a shield to honestly not be let down or really caught off guard by people. 
I know that’s not really healthy😅😅 but I’ve acknowledged it and have been more mindful of my nature and habits. 
Even with fitness I sometimes focus on the negatives with the world of influencers and bodybuilding as a whole. 
It is one thing that is for certain,  this lifestyle has brought me and family so much Joy. 
I pray that people find a passion or something that gives back to self and others around you. 
Familyandmuscle gives me that and so much more.
